### Smart Task - DashboardController API Test
### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

### Auth
@accessToken = REPLACE_ACCESS_TOKEN

### Dynamic IDs
@projectId = REPLACE_PROJECT_ID

### 1) Get my dashboard (assigned tasks summary)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/dashboard/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Description:
### - totalAssignedTasks: How many tasks are assigned to me
### - completedTasks: Count of finished tasks (highest status position)
### - overdueTasks: Tasks past deadline, not completed
### - dueSoonTasks: Deadline within 7 days, not completed
### - tasksByPriority: Grouping of {priority: count}
### - tasksByStatus: Grouping of {statusName: count}

### 2) Get project dashboard (team progress)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/dashboard/projects/{{projectId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Description:
### - projectId, projectName: Project reference
### - completionPercentage: (completedTasks / totalTasks) * 100.0
### - totalTasks / completedTasks: Counters
### - tasksByStatus: Grouping of {statusName: count}
### - tasksByPriority: Grouping of {priority: count}

### Quick setup to test:
### A) Create project via ProjectController
### B) Create multiple tasks with priorities (high/medium/low) via TaskController
### C) Assign tasks to team members
### D) Move some tasks to Done status via KanbanController
### E) Call endpoint (1) to see personal stats
### F) Call endpoint (2) to see project completion %
